# Plan File Standards

Every `.plan.md` file must include a **plan log header** immediately after the YAML frontmatter and before the main heading.

## Plan Log Header Format

```markdown
> **Plan** | `<plan-name>`
> **Status** | `<status>` | **Priority** | `<priority>`
> **Created** | `<YYYY-MM-DD>` | **Updated** | `<YYYY-MM-DD>`
> **Author** | `<author>` | **Environment** | `<environments>`
> **PR/Ticket** | `<link or —>` | **Rollback** | `<Yes/No/N/A>`
```

## Status Lifecycle

| Status | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| `Draft` | Plan created, still being designed or edited |
| `In Review` | Submitted for peer/team review |
| `Approved` | Reviewed and approved for execution |
| `In Progress` | Actively being executed |
| `Completed` | All tasks finished and verified |
| `On Hold` | Paused due to blocker or external dependency |
| `Cancelled` | Plan abandoned, will not be executed |
| `Rolled Back` | Was applied but changes were reverted |

## Priority Levels

| Priority | Use when |
|----------|----------|
| `P1 - Critical` | Production outage, security vulnerability |
| `P2 - High` | Blocking work, time-sensitive changes |
| `P3 - Medium` | Planned work, scheduled changes |
| `P4 - Low` | Nice-to-have, cleanup, optimization |

## Rules
- Always set status when creating or updating a plan
- Update the `Updated` date on every status change
- Move status forward: Draft → In Review → Approved → In Progress → Completed
- Add PR/Ticket link once available
